This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as it deals with autonomous driving tasks and the comparison of deep learning architectures for such tasks. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) as it focuses on the performance of different deep learning architectures.
